dataqual.logic: Precincts represented as interlocking, non overlapping polygons covering the state of Minnesota. Some small slivers exist as of July 2008. Features with a Precinct_Num of 0 are areas required by statute to have a separate precinct, but which do not have an official precinct in the Statewide Voter Registration System.
dataqual.complete: Continually updated as precinct boundaries are modified based on notifications the Office of the Secretary of State receives from municipalities and counties about precinct boundary changes and annexations. All precinct boundary changes needed to be passed by municipalities by June 1, 2008 for the 2008 General Election. This dataset includes all precinct boundary changes the Office has been notified of as of the date of publication.

horizpa.horizpar: Changes to precinct data are recorded mostly from paper maps, no determination of spatial accuracy has been made. Counties where precincts are drawn to follow Lawrence Group data generally are more spatially accurate.
